how to sleep better throughout the night with twins my twins are months now and still wake up every after their am feeding but after their am and bedtime at pm their fine they sleep for hours its making me very tired and they also wake each other up with one is crying what can i do please help thanks the only thing i can tell you is that it does get better with time i had to give my twins rice cereal in their bottles for their gerd and trust me it didnt help them sleep any better they still woke up every hours at least you are getting a hour stretch you are lucky there around or so months things start to get easier at that point the bottles get fewer and fewer till you can stop them completely but for now all you can do is grin and bear it nothing you can really do about them waking each other up my twins are months old and if one is screaming in the night the other still wakes up they will never grow completely immune to it but they do learn to ignore it some try putting them in seperate cribs if you havent already but yeah thats twins they are really hard in the beginning but they do get easier Sleep Breastfeeding Episodes of Lost (Season 1) The Amber Spyglass Shaggy dog story She Loves You Sin City Futurama (TV series - season 5) Knots Landing Days of our Lives Indianapolis 500 Bart chalkboard gags Daylight saving time Avenue Q Narcolepsy Social rule Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Jon Secada Characters of The Sandman Sudden infant death syndrome The Marshall Mathers LP Kimi Finster Anne Rice The Apprentice 2 The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Bread Waiting for Godot Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Waking the Dragons Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Insomnia The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time characters Blood (computer game) Shark W.I.T.C.H. The Lovely Bones Urinary incontinence Jam (TV series) Apollo 8 Rapid eye movement Gastroesophageal reflux disease Childbirth Hansel und Gretel Chronic fatigue syndrome Sleep debt Siesta Thermal power station T